---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { LAST_REVIEWED, entries } from '../data';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

const REPO_URL = 'https://github.com/donjguido/small-to-large-model-monitoring-frontier';
const ISSUES_BASE = `${REPO_URL}/issues/new?template`;
---
<Layout title="About — Monitoring Frontier AI" description="Provenance, scope, maintenance, and how to contribute.">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a href={`${base}/`}>← Home</a></div>
  <h1>About this review</h1>
  <p><strong>Last reviewed:</strong> <span class="mono">{LAST_REVIEWED}</span> · <strong>{entries.length}</strong> bibliography entries</p>

  <h2>What this is</h2>
  <p>
    I prepared this as a gift for a friend who wanted a way in to the
    subfield, and I'm making it public in case it's useful to other people
    in the same position. <strong>It is not a professional or hard-set
    report.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    The review was compiled by Claude (Anthropic's AI assistant) via a
    structured deep-research task, framed and arranged by
    <strong>donjguido</strong>. <strong>I did not independently review the
    underlying sources</strong> — the annotations and the critical
    assessment reflect Claude's read of the literature, not mine. It is
    not peer-reviewed, not a multi-author consensus document, and should
    be treated as a starting point for further reading rather than an
    authoritative field summary. A single-curator AI-assisted compilation,
    produced in hours rather than months.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Corrections welcome.</strong> If something is wrong, outdated,
    or missing, please file an issue using one of the templates below — a
    maintainer edits the YAML in <code>/data</code> and the site rebuilds.
  </p>

  <h2>Scope and honest limitations</h2>
  <p>
    This review covers the subfield of runtime monitoring of frontier AI
    models — specifically the use of smaller or weaker models, and small
    probes trained on internal activations, to flag misbehavior in larger
    models. Annotations are concise, coverage prioritizes the most-cited
    and most-recent work, and no attempt is made at systematic literature-
    search completeness. Claims are sourced to the underlying papers; the
    <a href={`${base}/critical-assessment/`}>critical assessment</a>
    reflects the compiler's honest read, not a community consensus.
  </p>

  <h2>Maintenance</h2>
  <p>
    This site is maintained ad-hoc via GitHub issues. It was current as of
    <span class="mono">{LAST_REVIEWED}</span> and may become stale. AI
    safety research moves monthly — if you notice an outdated claim, a
    broken link, a missing foundational paper, or a replication that
    updates a cited result, please open an issue. Issues are the canonical
    way to propose changes.
  </p>

  <h2>How to contribute</h2>
  <p>Open an issue using one of the templates below:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${ISSUES_BASE}=suggest-entry.yml`}>Suggest a new bibliography entry</a></li>
    <li><a href={`${ISSUES_BASE}=flag-outdated.yml`}>Flag an outdated or superseded claim</a></li>
    <li><a href={`${ISSUES_BASE}=report-broken-link.yml`}>Report a broken link</a></li>
    <li><a href={`${ISSUES_BASE}=other.yml`}>Anything else</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data</h2>
  <p>The bibliography and taxonomy live in YAML files in the repo. Machine-readable exports are also published as JSON:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${base}/data/entries.json`}>entries.json</a> — every bibliography record</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}/data/taxonomy.json`}>taxonomy.json</a> — the category tree</li>
    <li>Source YAML: <a href={`${REPO_URL}/tree/main/data`}>data/ in the repo</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to cite</h2>
  <pre style="background:#f4ece6; padding:0.8rem 1rem; font-size:0.82rem; overflow-x:auto; border-left:2px solid var(--accent);">donjguido. "Monitoring Frontier AI."
Compiled with Claude (Anthropic). {LAST_REVIEWED}.
URL: [deploy URL]</pre>
  <p style="color:var(--fg-muted); font-size:0.92rem;">
    When citing individual findings, cite the underlying paper directly —
    this review is an orientation layer, not a primary source.
  </p>

  <h2>License</h2>
  <p>
    Text content is released under
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">CC BY 4.0</a>;
    site source code is MIT.
  </p>

  <h2>Source repository</h2>
  <p>Site source, data files, and issue templates: <a href={REPO_URL}>donjguido/small-to-large-model-monitoring-frontier</a></p>
</Layout>
